title: Settings Sub-Screens i18n — AccountSecurity, 2FA, Engine, Settings Loading
description: |
  Replace all hardcoded strings in settings-related sub-screens.

  FILE: account-security-screen.tsx
    Add: import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next'
    Add: const { t } = useTranslation()  inside component
    Note: SETTINGS_ROWS is a static const array outside component — move it INSIDE
    the component function so t() can be called, OR replace label strings with
    t() calls at render time by mapping row.labelKey → t(row.labelKey).
    Recommended: add `labelKey` field to each row object and render t(row.labelKey).

    SETTINGS_ROWS label keys:
      'Region'                    → accountSecurity.region
      'Email Address'             → accountSecurity.email
      'Third-Party Voice…'        → accountSecurity.thirdPartyVoice
      'tuya_voice_openapi'        → (keep as-is, technical name)
      'Change Login Password'     → accountSecurity.changePassword
      'Face ID'                   → accountSecurity.faceId
      'Pattern Lock'              → accountSecurity.patternLock
      'Multi-Device Login…'       → accountSecurity.multiDevice
      'Two-Factor Authentication' → accountSecurity.twoFactor
      'User Code'                 → accountSecurity.userCode
      'Delete Account'            → accountSecurity.deleteAccount

    Static values to translate:
      'Ukraine'     (value) → keep as-is (proper noun)
      'Linked'      (value) → t('accountSecurity.emailLinked')
      'Out of Sync' (value) → t('accountSecurity.outOfSync')
      'Not Set'     (value) → t('accountSecurity.notSet')
      'Off'         (value) → t('accountSecurity.statusOff')

    setHeaderViewState title: 'Account and Security' → t('accountSecurity.title')

    handleRowClick string comparisons: update to use labelKey or id checks (not label string).

    Dialog — Assign Email:
      DialogTitle 'Assign Email'        → t('accountSecurity.assignEmail')
      Input placeholder 'New Email Address' → t('accountSecurity.emailPlaceholder')
      Button 'Cancel'                   → t('common.cancel')
      Button 'Save changes'             → t('accountSecurity.saveChanges')
      toast.error('Email is required')  → t('accountSecurity.errors.emailRequired')
      toast.success('Email assigned…')  → t('accountSecurity.errors.emailSaved')
      toast.error('Failed to assign…')  → t('accountSecurity.errors.emailFailed')

    Dialog — Change Password:
      DialogTitle 'Change Password'     → t('accountSecurity.changePassword')
      Placeholders: current/new/confirm → t('accountSecurity.currentPassword') etc.
      Buttons: Cancel / Save changes    → t('common.cancel') / t('accountSecurity.saveChanges')
      Toasts: all 4 → accountSecurity.errors.*

  FILE: two-factor-auth-screen.tsx
    Add: import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next'
    Add: const { t } = useTranslation()
    setHeaderViewState title → t('settings.twoFactorAuth')   [key exists ✓]
    'Enhance Your Security'  → t('twoFactor.title')
    Description paragraph    → t('twoFactor.subtitle')
    'Google Authenticator'   → t('twoFactor.googleAuth')
    'Use Google App…'        → t('twoFactor.googleAuthSub')
    'Enabled'/'Disabled'     → t('common.enabled') / t('common.disabled')
    'How it works'           → t('twoFactor.howItWorks')
    Step 1/2/3 spans         → t('twoFactor.step1') / t('twoFactor.step2') / t('twoFactor.step3')
    toast.success/error msgs → t('twoFactor.errors.toggleFailed') etc.

  FILE: engine-screen/EngineScreen.tsx
    Add: import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next'
    Add: const { t } = useTranslation()
    Header title → t('engine.title') (use vehicle.name interpolation: t('engine.title') + ': ' + name)
    'Not Available' h2        → t('engine.notAvailable')
    No-permission message     → t('engine.noPermission')
    Not-equipped message      → t('engine.notEquipped')
    'Go Back' button          → t('common.goBack')
    'Engine is UNOPEN/OPEN' → t('engine.statusUnOPEN') / t('engine.statusOPEN')
    'Current connection…'     → t('engine.connectionInfo')
    'Lock Engine (Safe Mode)' → t('engine.lockSafe')
    'Emergency Block!'        → t('engine.emergencyBlock')
    'Unlock Engine'           → t('engine.unlock')
    window.confirm strings    → t('engine.confirm.lock') / t('engine.confirm.emergency') etc.
    showToast messages        → t('engine.success.OPEN') / t('engine.errors.actionFailed') etc.
    'Failed to check permissions' → t('engine.errors.checkFailed')

  FILE: settings-screen.tsx
    Lines 273-274: 'Loading settings…' → t('settings.loading')
    Line 284: 'Retry'                  → t('common.retry')
    (useTranslation already imported ✓)

